response.Q3: The cost for clicking on nodes varied between nodes.

response.Q0: I wanted to settle for at least between 6o-something to 90-something dollars when selecting my node.
response.Q1: Yes, I forgot most of the time, but when i did remember, I would stop clicking on another node if I saw a node having a range from 60 dollars and/or up.
response.Q2: It wasn't difficult, but anxiety caused me to click on another node and thus waste more money, even when I already clicked on a desired node(with my appropriate dollar amount) prior. Obviously, the random node amount on each stage made it difficult, especially if all 3 revealed nodes were a red negative digit:(

response.Q0: Everything was clear and easy to understand.
response.Q1: This is my very first time participating in a Web of Cash HIT.
response.Q2: I thoroughly enjoyed the game and appreciate the opportunity to have participated in this study. Thank you kindly, as I am currently unemployed for a while now. God bless you.
